%20discussions%20about%20sexual%20orientation%20or%20gender%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fallaccess.collegeboard.org%2Four-commitment-ap-students-families-and-educators%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20College%20Board%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0it%20would%20not%20modify%20the%20AP%20Psychology%20curriculum%20to%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20law%20after%20the%20Florida%20State%20Board%20of%20Education%20requested%20that%20the%20organization%20audit%20the%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nonprofit%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20modifying%20the%20coursework%20would%20%26quot%3Bbreak%20the%20fundamental%20promise%20of%20AP%26quot%3B%20and%20colleges%20would%20no%20longer%20broadly%20accept%20the%20work%20for%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20College%20Board%2C%20since%20it%20was%20first%20launched%2030%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20section%20of%20the%20AP%20Psychology%20course%20has%20asked%20students%20to%20%26quot%3Bdescribe%20how%20sex%20and%20gender%20influence%20socialization%20and%20other%20aspects%20of%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20on%20August%203%2C%20it%20began%20advising%20schools%20not%20to%20teach%20the%20course%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20stay%20within%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20advise%20Florida%20districts%20not%20to%20offer%20AP%20Psychology%20until%20Florida%20reverses%20their%20decision%20and%20allows%20parents%20and%20students%20to%20choose%20to%20take%20the%20full%20course%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20August%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20day%20later%20the%20Florida%20teacher's%20union%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-teachers-union-ap-psych-course-criticizes-desantis-administration-2023-8%5C%22%3Eaccused%20DeSantis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20using%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremist%20agenda%26quot%3B%20to%20censor%20the%20AP%20Psychology%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20we%20possibly%20take%20this%20away%20from%20kids%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20AP%20Psychology%20teacher%20in%20Broward%20asked.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20than%20talking%20about%20gender%2C%20although%20that's%20obviously%20an%20important%20place%20for%20kids%20as%20well%2C%20to%20be%20able%20to%20discuss%20that%20or%20learn%20stuff%20about%20that.%20But%20it's%20not%20just%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20teacher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20teacher%20said%20AP%20Psychology%20also%20helps%20students%20get%20mental%20health%20information%20they%20wouldn't%20have%20access%20to%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPoliticians%20are%20constantly%20making%20decisions%20on%20material%20that%20we%20teach%20and%20telling%20us%20the%20kids%20aren't%20ready%20to%20hear%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20I%20can%20get%20into%20that%20because%20I%20feel%20like%20I'm%20getting%20in%20trouble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGosh%2C%20I've%20never%20had%20to%20think%20about%20that%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20teacher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-ap-psychology-teacher-afraid-dont-say-gay-bill-desantis-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691689896000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3e568a8ce53001a594504%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-ap-psychology-teacher-afraid-dont-say-gay-bill-desantis-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Florida%20schools%20are%20canceling%20AP%20Psychology%20courses%20because%20they%20might%20break%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3BDon't%20Say%20Gay%26quot%3B%20law%20signed%20by%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-ap-psychology-te