o%20a%20question%20by%20BJP%20MP%20CM%20Ramesh%2C%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Environment%20Ashwini%20Kumar%20Choubey%20told%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20that%20India%20is%20doing%20far%20more%20than%20its%20fair%20share%20to%20combat%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloped%20countries%20have%20consumed%20more%20than%2080%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20global%20carbon%20budget%20(since%201850)%20for%20limiting%20average%20temperature%20rise%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20by%202100%2C%20leaving%20countries%20like%20India%20with%20%26quot%3Bvery%20little%20carbon%20space%20for%20the%20future%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERich%20nations%20are%20%26quot%3Beating%20into%20even%20this%20reduced%20entitlement%26quot%3B%20for%20India.%20Despite%20this%2C%20India%20has%20chosen%20to%20walk%20its%20climate%20talk%2C%20conscious%20of%20the%20need%20to%20pioneer%20a%20sustainable%20development%20pathway%20for%20the%20entire%20globe%2C%20while%20attending%20to%20the%20needs%20and%20aspirations%20of%20its%20people%2C%20economy%20and%20society%2C%20he%20said.%20C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20science%20defines%20carbon%20budget%20as%20the%20amount%20of%20greenhouse%20gases%20that%20can%20be%20emitted%20for%20a%20given%20level%20of%20global%20warming%20(1.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20this%20case).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20annual%20emissions%20are%20well%20below%20the%20three%20leading%20emitters%20-%20China%2C%20the%20US%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20--%20and%20its%20per%20capita%20emissions%20are%20much%20below%20the%20world%20average.%20The%20country%20accounts%20for%20less%20than%204%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20global%20cumulative%20emissions%20from%201850%20until%202019%2C%20Mr%20Choubey%20told%20the%20Upper%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%202.4%20tCO2e%20(tonne%20carbon%20dioxide%20equivalent)%2C%20India's%20per%20capita%20greenhouse%20gas%20emission%20is%20far%20below%20the%20global%20average%20of%206.3%20tCO2e%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20released%20last%20year%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Environment%20Programme.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPer%20capita%20emission%20in%20the%20US%20(14%20tCO2e)%20is%20far%20above%20the%20global%20average%2C%20followed%20by%20Russia%20(13%20tCO2e)%2C%20China%20(9.7%20tCO2e)%2C%20Brazil%20and%20Indonesia%20(about%207.5%20tCO2e%20each)%2C%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20(7.2%20tCO2e).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20national%20emissions%20must%20be%20judged%20both%20by%20equity%20in%20mitigation%20and%20in%20the%20light%20of%20climate%20actions%20being%20undertaken.%20On%20both%20grounds%2C%20India%2C%20relative%20to%20its%20responsibility%20and%20relative%20to%20what%20equity%20demands%2C%20is%20doing%20far%20more%20than%20its%20fair%20share%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Choubey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20updated%20its%20nationally%20determined%20contributions%20--%20national%20plans%20to%20limit%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20--%20in%20August%20last%20year%2C%20promising%20to%20reduce%20emissions%20intensity%20of%20GDP%20by%2045%20per%20cent%20by%202030%2C%20from%20the%202005%20level%2C%20and%20achieve%2050%20per%20cent%20cumulative%20electric%20power%20installed%20capacity%20from%20non-fossil%20fuel-based%20energy%20resources%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20climate%20actions%20have%20so%20far%20been%20largely%20financed%20through%20domestic%20resources%2C%20the%20minister%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Paris%20climate%20talks%20in%202015%2C%20countries%20agreed%20to%20limit%20global%20warming%20to%201.5%20degrees%20Celsius%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20pre-industrial%20levels%20to%20avoid%20extreme%2C%20destructive%20and%20likely%20irreversible%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarth's%20global%20surface%20temperature%20has%20risen%20by%20around%201.15%20degrees%20Celsius%20and%20the%20carbon%20dioxide%20spewed%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20industrial%20revolution%20is%20closely%20tied%20to%20it.%20In%20the%20business-as-usual%20scenario%2C%20the%20world%20is%20heading%20for%20a%20temperature%20rise%20of%20around%203%20degrees%20Celsius%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClimate%20science%20says%20the%20world%20must%20halve%20emissions%20by%202030%20from%20the%202009%20levels%20to%20keep%20the%20chances%20of%20achieving%20the%201.5-degrees%20target%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20countries%20argue%20that%20wealthier%20nations%20should%20take%20greater%20responsibility%20for%20emission%20reductions%2C%20given%20their%20historical%20emissions%2C%20and%20provide%20the%20necessary%20means%20of%20implementation%2C%20including%20finance%20and%20technology%2C%20to%20assist%20developing%20and%20vulnerable%20nations%20in%20the%20transition%20to%20clean%20energy%20and%20adapting%20to%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Copenhagen%20UN%20climate%20talks%20in%202009%2C%20developed%20countries%20had%20promised%20to%20provide%20%24100%20billion%20per%20year%20by%202020%20to%20help%20developing%20countries%20combat%20climate%20change.%20The%20failure%20to%20deliver%20this%20commitment%20at%20successive%20climate%20talks%20has%20eroded%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20latest%20assessment%20of%20delivery%20plans%2C%20the%20%24100%20billion%20commitment%20will%20be%20met%20only%20in%202023%2C%20three%20years%20past%20the%20target%20date%2C%20and%20only%20then%20mainly%20because%20of%20increased%20financing%20from%20the%20multilateral%20development%20banks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBilateral%20public%20finance%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20important%20indicator%20of%20the%20direct%20contribution%20by%20developed%20countries%2C%20has%20not%20increased%20measurably%20since%202016%20and%20there%20remain%20important%20shortfalls%20in%20its%20quality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20