%80%99Office%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1768)%20has%20recipes%20for%20truffle%2C%20saffron%20and%20various%20cheese-flavoured%20ice%20creams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20history%20of%20ice%20cream%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Marshall%20was%20publishing%2C%20ice%20cream%20was%20far%20more%20accessible%20to%20the%20public%20than%20in%20earlier%20centuries.%20Prior%20to%20the%201800s%2C%20ice%20was%20collected%20from%20frozen%20waterways%20and%20stored%20in%20underground%20ice%20houses%2C%20largely%20restricted%20to%20large%20estates%20with%20the%20necessary%20land%2C%20wealth%20and%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%201820s%2C%20however%2C%20ice%20was%20imported%20to%20Britain%20from%20Europe%20and%20then%20the%20US%20and%20stored%20in%20ice%20wells%20and%20warehouses.%20The%20importation%20of%20larger%20stocks%20of%20ice%20reduced%20costs%2C%20while%20simultaneously%2C%20innovators%20were%20designing%20apparatus%20for%20mechanical%20freezing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20547px)%2085vw%2C%20547px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10195244%2Fimage-1209.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22547%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10195244%2Fimage-1209.png%20547w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10195244%2Fimage-1209-188x300.png%20188w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667548%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22872%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAn%20advertisement%20for%20Marshall%E2%80%99s%20patent%20freezer%20from%201885.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20a%20long%20time%20until%20ice%20was%20easily%20produced%20within%20the%20home%2C%20but%20cheaper%20ice%20made%20ice%20cream%20more%20readily%20available%20and%20implements%20were%20devised%20so%20it%20could%20be%20made%20at%20home.%20Both%20Emy%20and%20Marshall%E2%80%99s%20cookbooks%20depicting%20ice%20cream%20makers%20and%20Marshall%E2%80%99s%20patent%20freezer%20enlisted%20the%20same%20freezing%20technique%20as%20Emy%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vam.ac.uk%2Fblog%2Fcreating-new-europe-1600-1800-galleries%2Fcan-i-have-a-taste-of-your-ice-cream%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESarbotiere%20et%20son%20Seau%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresearch.colonialwilliamsburg.org%2FFoundation%2Fjournal%2FSpring10%2Ficecream.cfm%5C%22%3Epot%20freezer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bucket).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIce%20and%20salt%20were%20placed%20around%20a%20bucket%2C%20within%20which%20a%20custard%20or%20water%20mixture%20was%20stirred%20or%20rotated%20until%20it%20froze.%20Marshall%E2%80%99s%20innovation%20was%20the%20shallow%20pan%2C%20which%20gave%20an%20increased%20surface%20area%20for%20faster%20freezing.%20Equipped%20with%20such%20a%20freezer%20(and%20perhaps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2Fb29314501%2Fpage%2F246%2Fmode%2F2up%5C%22%3EMarshall%E2%80%99s%20patent%20Ice%20Cave%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20storing%20the%20ices)%2C%20middle-class%20housewives%20could%20produce%20ice%20cream%20in%20their%20own%20kitchens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIce%20cream%20and%20leisure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIce%20cream%20is%20well-suited%20for%20engaging%20visitors%20at%20heritage%20properties%20today%2C%20not%20because%20of%20the%20history%20of%20how%20it%20was%20produced%20within%20the%20home%20but%20because%20of%20its%20holiday%20connotations.%20Whether%20it%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9C99%E2%80%9D%2C%20an%20%E2%80%9Coyster%E2%80%9D%20enjoyed%20at%20the%20beach%2C%20or%20the%20nearing%20jingle%20of%20an%20ice%20cream%20truck%2C%20ice%20cream%20has%20clear%20cultural%20and%20emotional%20links%20to%20recreation%20and%20enjoyment.%20This%20was%20also%20true%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%2019th%20century%20Britain%2C%20street%20vendors%20(many%20of%20them%20Italian%20immigrants)%20began%20selling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscarboroughmuseumsandgalleries.org.uk%2Fobject%2Fpenny-lick-glasses%2F%5C%22%3Epenny%20licks%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9Chokey-pokey%E2%80%9D%20from%20stalls%20or%20carts%20in%20the%20streets.%20In%20contrast%20to%20the%20immaculately%20moulded%20delicacies%20in%20Marshall%E2%80%99s%20cookbook%20%E2%80%93%20which%20required%20the%20purchase%20of%20several%20pieces%20of%20equipment%20%E2%80%93%20this%20ice%20cream%20was%20to%20be%20enjoyed%20while%20out%20and%20about.%20It%20was%20also%20cheap%2C%20as%20implied%20by%20%E2%80%9Cpenny%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20title.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECustomers%20would%20purchase%20their%20ice%20upon%20a%20glass%20%E2%80%9Click%E2%80%9D%2C%20eat%20it%20and%20then%20return%20the%20lick%20to%20the%20vendor%20for%20reuse.%20With%20growing%20numbers%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fhistory%2Fbritish%2Fvictorians%2Fseaside_01.shtml%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DMost%2520of%2520our%2C%2527traditional%2527%2520summer%2520holiday.%5C%22%3Eseaside%20resorts%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20leisure%20industry%20over%20the%2019th%20century%2C%20ices%20were%20enjoyed%20while%20on%20holiday%20or%20daily%20excursions%20and%20at%20public%20events%20like%20exhibitions%20or%20fairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10200540%2Fimage-1210.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22920%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10200540%2Fimage-1210.png%20920w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10200540%2Fimage-1210-300x189.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667552%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22580%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChildren%20surround%20an%20ice%20cream%20vendor%20in%201909.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20portability%20of%20ice%20cream%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20culinary%20appeal%2C%20that%20has%20led%20to%20its%20lasting%20place%20in%20our%20leisure%20time%20%E2%80%93%20a%20delicious%20treat%20that%20can%20be%20enjoyed%2C%20one-handed%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20larger%20experience.%20The%20act%20of%20eating%20ice%20cream%20prepared%20from%20a%20Georgian%20or%20Victorian%20recipe%20therefore%20connects%20today%E2%80%99s%20visitors%20to%20a%20long%20tradition%20of%20enjoying%20ices%20recreationally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20heritage%20properties%20are%20unlikely%20to%20embrace%20the%20more%20unsanitary%20ways%20ice%20cream%20used%20to%20be%20eaten%2C%20serving%20up%20historical%20recipes%20gives%20visitors%20a%20chance%20to%20savour%20a%20new%20sensory%20layer%20of%20the%20past.%20That%20taste%20can%20be%20linked%20into%20larger%20histories.%20From%20ice%20cream%2C%20we%20can%20learn%20about%20technological%20developments%2C%20changing%20attitudes%20towards%20sanitation%2C%20global%20travel%2C%20the%20availability%20of%20ingredients%20throughout%20time%2C%20trends%2C%20fashion%20and%20leisure%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelving%20into%20the%20history%20of%20food%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20tins%20in%20our%20cupboards%2C%20to%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%2C%20or%20an%20ice%20cream%20at%20the%20beach%20%E2%80%93%20can%20bring%20new%20perspective%20to%20both%20the%20past%20and%20the%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Flindsay-middleton-1457823%5C%22%3ELindsay%20Middleton%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Food%20Historian%20and%20Knowledge%20Exchange%20Associate%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-glasgow-1269%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Glasgow%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20