12937285%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Sundarbans%20Nears%20Tiger%20Carrying%20Capacity%2C%20Indian%20Authorities%20Want%20Cooperation%20With%20Bangladesh%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10151111%2FTiger-in-the-Sundarbans.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Tigers%20in%20the%20Indian%20Sundarbans%20may%20soon%20need%20their%20own%20%E2%80%98Look%20East%E2%80%99%20policy%20owing%20to%20a%20space%20crunch%20on%20this%20side%20of%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20finding%20was%20part%20of%20a%20report%20prepared%20by%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA)%20and%20the%20Wildlife%20Institute%20of%20India%20(WII)%20titled%20%E2%80%98Status%20of%20Tigers%3A%20Co-Predators%20and%20Prey%20in%20India%2C%202022%E2%80%99.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Findias-tiger-population-rises-to-3167-reveals-latest-census-data%5C%22%3Esummary%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20April%2C%20had%20estimated%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20tiger%20population%20stood%20at%203%2C167%20%E2%80%93%20an%20increase%20of%206.7%25%20from%20the%20previous%20census%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20report%20was%20released%20recently%2C%20which%C2%A0estimates%20that%20the%20population%20density%20of%20tigers%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Sundarban%20forests%20has%20reached%204.27%20per%20100%20square%20kilometres.%20That%20number%20is%20close%20to%20the%20mangrove%20forests%E2%80%99%20estimated%20carrying%20capacity%20of%204.68%20tigers%20per%20100%20square%20kilometres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Sundarbans%20are%20bound%20by%20human%20habitation%20to%20their%20north%20and%20west%2C%20the%20report%20notes%2C%20an%20expanding%20tiger%20population%20can%20only%20move%20further%20east%20into%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20forests%20(the%20Sundarbans%20border%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20in%20the%20south).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20forests%20are%20situated%20along%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20delta%2C%20formed%20by%20the%20rivers%20Ganga%2C%20Brahmaputra%20and%20Meghna%2C%20and%20are%20divided%20among%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20with%20the%20latter%20accounting%20for%2058%25%20of%20their%20total%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20tigers%20are%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20only%20ones%20known%20to%20live%20in%20a%20mangrove%20habitat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPhotos%20from%20camera%20traps%20across%20the%20forests%20revealed%20the%20presence%20of%20100%20individual%20tigers%20as%20of%202022%20%E2%80%93%2081%20from%20the%20Sundarban%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%2020%20from%20the%20adjoining%20South%2024%20Parganas%20district%20of%20West%20Bengal%20state%20(one%20tiger%20was%20common%20to%20both%20areas).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20says%20that%20while%20tigers%20may%20move%20into%20Bangladesh%20through%20select%20areas%20within%20the%20forest%2C%20the%20two%20neighbouring%20countries%20protect%20the%20animals%20using%20different%20parameters.%20Major%20parts%20of%20the%20Indian%20Sundarbans%20are%20under%20the%20highest%20protection%20and%20management%20regime%20associated%20with%20a%20tiger%20reserve%2C%20with%20some%20parts%20set%20aside%20for%20forest%20produce%20extraction%20and%20tourism.%20In%20Bangladesh%2C%20there%20are%20three%20small%20sanctuaries%20which%20act%20as%20wildlife%20%E2%80%98hotspots%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20forest%20is%20open%20to%20harvesting%20of%20forest%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%5BA%5D%20possible%20conduit%20for%20the%20tigers%20towards%20%5Bthe%5D%20east%20would%20be%20the%20channels%20which%20are%20less%20than%20400m%20wide%20and%20situated%20at%20the%20northern%20part%20of%20Basirhat%20range%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20continues%20to%20say%20that%20cooperation%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20will%20be%20necessary%20to%20protect%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20ecology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTrans-boundary%20cooperation%20and%20knowledge%20sharing%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20are%20important%20to%20maintain%20ecological%20integrity%20of%20the%20landscape.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20to%20explore%20areas%20within%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20for%20tiger%20relocation%20as%20well%20as%20prey%20augmentation%2C%20as%20the%20population%20is%20nearing%20%5Bthe%5D%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20current%20prey%20density.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Flatest-census-data-insufficient-to-draw-any-conclusions-on-tiger-numbers-say-experts%5C%22%3ELatest%20Census%20Data%20%E2%80%98Insufficient%E2%80%99%20to%20Draw%20Any%20Conclusions%20on%20Tiger%20Numbers%2C%20Say%20Experts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20Sundarban%20Tiger%20Reserve%20is%20home%20to%20a%20high%20number%20of%20tigers%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3EDown%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.downtoearth.org.in%2Fnews%2Fwildlife-biodiversity%2Fsundarbans-has-been-slipping-in-rank-despite-an-increased-tiger-count-here-s-why-88777%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20its%20ranking%20among%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20tiger%20reserves%20has%20fallen%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Sundarban%20reserve%20has%20done%20well%20in%20containing%20poaching%20and%20tiger-human%20conflict%2C%20staff%20shortage%20still%20remains%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leader%20of%20a%20different%20report%20the%20NTCA%20and%20WII%20prepared%20last%20year%20also%20emphasised%20the%20need%20for%20more%20staff%20and%20trans-border%20cooperation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20to%20improve%20the%20staff%20strength%2C%20which%20was%20about%2050%25%20when%20it%20was%20evaluated.%20The%20lack%20of%20enough%20staff%20is%20affecting%20many%20areas%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20%3Cem%3EDown%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20area%20development%20committees%20need%20to%20become%20functional%20under%20divisional%20commissioners%20to%20monitor%20illegal%20tourism.%20Over%20and%20above%2C%20more%20management%20coordination%20is%20required%20between%20India%20and%20Bangladesh%20Sundarbans%20forest%20areas.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDown%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20spoke%20to%20officials%20working%20in%20the%20Sundarban%20reserve%2C%20who%20said%20that%20efforts%20were%20on%20to%20increase%20the%20size%20of%20the%20reserve%2C%20which%20would%20ultimately%20result%20in%20staff%20receiving%20stronger%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691665556000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10151111%2FTiger-in-the-Sundarbans.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsundarbans-capacity-tigers-cooperation-bangladesh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20report%20prepared%20by%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20and%20the%20Wildlife%20Institute%20of%20India%20estimates%20that%20the%20population%20density%20of%20tigers%20in%20India's%20Sundarban%20forests%20has%20reached%204.27%20per%20100%20sq%20km%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0against%20the%20estimated%20carrying%20capacity%20of%204.68.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fsundarbans-capacity-tigers-cooperation-bangladesh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20Moves%20New%20Bill%20on%20Appointment%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%2C%20CJI%20Excluded%20From%20Panel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2FElection_Commission_P1TI.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20introduced%20a%20Bill%20on%20Thursday%20that%20proposes%20that%20election%20commissioners%20will%20be%20selected%20by%20a%20panel%20led%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20with%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20as%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20comes%20after%20a%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20top%20court%20in%20March%20this%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-says-committee-of-pm-leader-of-opposition-cji-should-appoint-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Eruled%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20election%20commissioners%20should%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20based%20on%20advice%20from%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI).%20That%20verdict%20was%20delivered%20in%20a%20batch%20of%20pleas%20seeking%20reforms%20in%20the%20process%20of%20appointing%20election%20commissioners%20since%20the%20executive%20enjoyed%20the%20power%20to%20make%20appointments%20in%20violation%20of%20Article%20324(2)%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20passing%20the%20order%2C%20the%20bench%20noted%20that%20there%20is%20no%20parliamentary%20law%20in%20place%20to%20lay%20down%20the%20selection%20procedure%20for%20election%20commissioners%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20its%20order%20was%20meant%20to%20fill%20the%20constitutional%20vacuum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20Other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%20Conditions%20of%20Service%20and%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1689562359210340353%5C%22%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20Thursday%20by%20Union%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20even%20as%20opposition%20parties%20claimed%20that%20it%20would%20destroy%20the%20constitutional%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrucially%2C%20the%20Bill%20proposes%20to%20replace%20the%20CJI%20in%20the%20selection%20committee%20with%20a%20Union%20minister%20who%20is%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20%E2%80%93%20giving%20effective%20control%20of%20the%20appointment%20of%20election%20commissioners%20to%20the%20executive%20once%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fbill-election-commission-members-appointment-process-explained-8885676%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20parliament%20has%20the%20power%20to%20nullify%20the%20effect%20of%20a%20court%20ruling%20by%20addressing%20the%20concerns%20flagged%20in%20the%20judgment%2C%20the%20law%20cannot%20be%20contradictory%20to%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20this%20case%2C%20the%20arrangement%20prescribed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20was%20specifically%20because%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98legislative%20vacuum%E2%80%99.%20Filling%20that%20vacuum%20is%20well%20within%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20parliament%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20newspaper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20since%20the%20court%20repeatedly%20emphasised%20the%20idea%20of%20an%20independent%20body%20to%20conduct%20elections%20in%20the%20judgment%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20LoP%20is%20outvoted%20even%20before%20the%20process%20begins%20may%20raise%20eyebrows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConstitutional%20lawyer%20Gautam%20Bhatia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgautambhatia88%2Fstatus%2F1689561801266970624%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20SC%20verdict%20held%20that%20executive%20dominance%20in%20the%20appointment%20of%20election%20commissioners%20was%20unconstitutional%20and%20that%20parliamentary%20law%20can%E2%80%99t%20breach%20that%20principle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20and%20other%20election%20commissioners%20shall%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20Selection%20Committee%20consisting%20of%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(a)%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20chairperson%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(b)%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%2C%20member%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(c)%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20adds%20that%20the%20search%20committee%20for%20election%20commissioners%20will%20be%20headed%20by%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%2C%20with%20two%20members%20who%20are%20not%20below%20the%20rank%20of%20secretary%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%20They%20will%20prepare%20a%20panel%20of%20five%20persons%20for%20consideration%20by%20the%20Selection%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20appointment%20of%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20shall%20not%20be%20invalid%20merely%20by%20reason%20of%20any%20vacancy%20in%20or%20any%20defect%20in%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Selection%20Committee%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Bill%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOpposition%20sees%20bid%20to%20control%20poll%20panel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReacting%20to%20the%20Bill%2C%20Congress%20leader%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20said%20that%20through%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20BJP%20wants%20to%20make%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20a%20%E2%80%98Modi%20Election%20Commission%E2%80%99.%20He%20decried%20the%20move%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98Black%20Day%E2%80%99%20for%20Indian%20Democracy%20and%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbrazen%20assault%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20and%20bulldozing%20of%20the%20Constitutional%20independence%20of%20ECI%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CECI%20will%20now%20be%20among%20the%20last%20Constitutional%20institutions%20to%20fall%20at%20the%20altar%20of%20usurpation%20of%20power%20by%20any%20or%20all%20means%20by%20an%20autocrat%20Prime%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20is%20an%20assault%20on%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20Judiciary%20%26amp%3B%20people%E2%80%99s%20rights%20to%20elect%20their%20own%20government%20in%20a%20fair%20and%20impartial%20manner%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Frssurjewala%2Fstatus%2F1689584558835191808%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20selection%20committee%20does%20not%20constitute%20a%20check%20and%20balance%20and%20will%20be%20an%20%E2%80%9Cempty%20formality%E2%80%9D%20since%20not%20a%20single%20cabinet%20minister%20will%20vote%20against%20the%20prime%20minister%20who%20nominated%20him%20or%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrinamool%20Congress%20leaders%20Saket%20Gokhale%20and%20Sushmita%20Dev%20said%20that%20it%20betrayed%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20control%20an%20independent%20panel%20like%20the%20ECI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShocking.%20BJP%20is%20rigging%20the%202024%20election%20openly.%20Modi%20government%20has%20again%20brazenly%20trampled%20upon%20an%20SC%20judgment%20and%20is%20making%20the%20Election%20Commission%20its%20own%20bunch%20of%20stooges.%20In%20the%20(EC%20appointment)%20Bill%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20Union%20Minister%20in%20the%20selection%20committee%20to%20appoint%20the%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20the%20two%20Election%20Commissioners%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gokhale%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSaketGokhale%2Fstatus%2F1689535547310518273%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20judgment%20had%20clearly%20noted%20that%20the%20Committee%20should%20be%20(A)%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20(B)%20the%20PM%20and%20(C)%20the%20Leader%20of%20the%20Opposition.%20In%20the%20Bill%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20replaced%20the%20CJI%20with%20a%20union%20minister.%20Basically%20now%2C%20Modi%20and%20one%20minister%20will%20appoint%20the%20entire%20Election%20Commission.%20This%20is%20a%20clear%20step%20towards%20rigging%20the%202024%20elections%20after%20fear%20has%20been%20struck%20into%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20heart%20by%20the%20united%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDev%20said%20said%20that%20while%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20will%20be%20a%20member%20of%20the%20selection%20panel%2C%20they%20are%20bound%20to%20be%20outnumbered%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20yet%20another%20way%20to%20control%20an%20institution%20which%20must%20be%20independent.%E2%80%9D%20she%20tweeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAAP%20MLA%20Saurabh%20Bharadwaj%20said%20that%20the%20Bill%20shows%20that%C2%A0Modi%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20trust%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAamAadmiParty%2Fstatus%2F1689583532291858432%5C%22%3Esaid%20at%20a%20press%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20why%20%5BModi%5D%20took%20the%20CJI%20out%20of%20the%20panel%20and%20presented%20a%20Bill%20that%20now%20says%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20a%20minister%20chosen%20by%20the%20PM%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20will%20be%20appoint%20election%20commissioners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20was%20first%20published%20at%2012%3A30%20pm%20on%20August%2010%2C%202023%20and%20republished%20at%204%3A20%20pm%20on%20the%20same%20day.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691664646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F10%2FElection_Commission_P1TI.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnew-bill-selection-of-election-commissioners%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20panel%20will%20be%20led%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20with%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20as%20members.%20Opposition%20parties%20slammed%20the%20move%20as%20bulldozing%20of%20the%20constitutional%20independence%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A38%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnew-bill-selection-of-election-commissioners%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Adani%20Enterprises%20denies%20reports%20of%20exiting%20%246%20billion%20venture%20with%20Wilmar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691663983000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-03%2F30%2Ffull%2F1680150976-9586.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-enterprises-denies-reports-of-exiting-6-billion-venture-with-wilmar-123081000510_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Earlier%20this%20week%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported%20that%20Adani%20Enterprises%20is%20exploring%20selling%20its%20stake%20in%20its%20consumer-staple%20joint%20venture%20with%20Wilmar%20International%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-enterprises-denies-reports-of-exiting-6-billion-venture-with-wilmar-123081000510_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-enterprises-denies-reports-of-exiting-6-billion-venture-with-wilmar-123081000510_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-enterprises-denies-reports-of-exiting-6-billion-venture-with-wilmar-123081000510_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Does%20the%20Military%20of%20Pakistan%20Have%20Any%20Intention%20of%20Letting%20its%20Grip%20Over%20Politics%20Ease%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F07221444%2FScreenshot-2023-06-07-at-10.13.10-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHad%20not%20former%20Pakistan%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20government%20been%20ousted%20by%20a%20vote%20of%20no%20confidence%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Persian%20word%C2%A0%3Cem%3Etoshakhana%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20its%20treasures%20would%20have%20remained%20elusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHis%20dishonesty%20has%20been%20established%20beyond%20doubt%2C%E2%80%9D%20Judge%20Humayun%20Dilawar%20wrote%20in%20the%20ruling%2C%20sentencing%20Khan%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison%20for%20misusing%20his%20premiership%20from%202018%20to%202022%20to%20buy%20and%20sell%20gifts%20from%20the%20Toshakhana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20(70)%20leader%20of%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20(PTI)%2C%20was%20arrested%20on%20August%205%2C%20and%20through%20a%20notification%20issued%20on%20August%208%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20Pakistan%20(ECP)%20disqualified%20him%20from%20holding%20public%20office%3A%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Imran%20Ahmed%20Khan%20Niazi%20is%20disqualified%20for%20a%20period%20of%20five%20years%20and%20is%20also%20de-notified%20as%20a%20returned%20candidate%20from%20constituency%20NA-45%20Kurram-I.%E2%80%9D%20(Subdivision%20of%20Kurram%20District%20in%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%20province)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%2C%20faces%20more%20than%20100%20cases%20of%20corruption%2C%20fraud%20and%20even%20assassination%20since%20his%20ouster%2C%20was%20previously%20detained%20in%20May.%20His%20arrest%20had%20set%20ablaze%20an%20intense%20political%20turmoil%2C%20with%20violent%20clashes%20between%20PTI%20supporters%20and%20police%2C%20and%20attacks%20on%20the%20habitually%20revered%20military%E2%80%99s%20installations.%20This%20time%2C%20he%20has%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20lead-up%20to%20general%20elections%2C%20which%20are%20scheduled%20to%20be%20held%20within%20the%20next%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20of%20dissolving%20the%20National%20Assembly%20(Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20lower%20house)%20will%20begin%20from%20August%209%2C%20three%20days%20before%20Prime%20Minister%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%E2%80%99s%20term%20ends.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20an%20early%20dissolution%2C%20the%20ECP%20is%20mandated%20to%20conduct%20general%20elections%20within%2090%20days.%20But%20the%20timely%20conduct%20of%20polls%20in%20Pakistan%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20dubitable%20undertaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20constitutional%20norms%20be%20followed%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20has%20a%20history%20of%20non-adherence%20to%20constitutional%20norms.%20The%20only%20democratic%20solution%20to%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20protracted%20political%20and%20economic%20crises%20is%20for%20a%20freely%20elected%20civilian%20government%20with%20a%20fresh%20mandate.%20The%20composition%20of%20the%20caretaker%20government%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20finalised.%20Once%20formed%2C%20will%20it%20be%20able%20to%20conduct%20polls%20within%20the%20constitutionally%20mandated%20period%20of%2090%20days%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%201%2C%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20Bureau%20of%20Statistics%20submitted%20to%20the%20Council%20of%20Common%20Interests%20(CCI)%20for%20approval%20of%20the%202023%20census.%20The%20ECP%20is%20required%20to%20carry%20out%20fresh%20delimitation%20of%20all%20the%20Assembly%20constituencies%20before%20the%20next%20general%20elections.%20The%20notification%20of%20the%202023%20census%20makes%20the%20delimitation%20process%20mandatory.%20Attendant%20to%20several%20constitutional%20and%20legal%20requirements%2C%20this%20will%20be%20time-consuming%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20situation%20wherein%20polls%20might%20not%20be%20held%20until%20early%202024.%20The%20interests%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(PPP)%20and%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League%20%E2%80%95%20Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20remain%20in%20deferring%20timely%20polls%2C%20lest%20the%20PTI%20make%20a%20strong%20showing.%20Their%20bet%20is%20that%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20disqualification%20and%20the%20delay%20in%20the%20elections%20would%20erode%20his%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fus-website-diplomatic-cable-imran-khan-foreign-conspiracy%5C%22%3EUS%20Site%20Publishes%20%E2%80%98Diplomatic%20Cable%E2%80%99%20at%20Heart%20of%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Foreign%20Conspiracy%E2%80%99%20Claim%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMilitary%20and%20political%20regression%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20was%20in%20power%2C%20Khan%20found%20in%20Qamar%20Javed%20Bajwa%2C%20then%20military%20chief%2C%20an%20ally%20for%20his%20campaign%20against%20corruption%2C%20primarily%20focused%20on%20punishing%20the%20Sharif%20(PML-N)%20and%20Bhutto%20(PPP)%20families.%20But%20the%20friendship%20soured%20because%20of%20bitter%20differences%20over%20issues%20such%20as%20who%20to%20appoint%20as%20the%20spymaster%2C%20and%20the%20extension%20of%20Bajwa%E2%80%99s%20tenure.%20During%20the%20May%209%20%E2%80%98protests%E2%80%99%20hundreds%20of%20Imran%20Khan%20supporters%20vandalised%20state%20buildings%2C%20including%20martyrs%E2%80%99%20monuments%20and%20sites%20such%20as%20the%20Army%20General%20Headquarters%20(GHQ)%20in%20Rawalpindi%20and%20the%20corps%20commander%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Lahore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20military%20vowed%20to%20tighten%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnoose%20of%20law%E2%80%9D%20around%20%E2%80%9Cplanners%20and%20masterminds%20who%20mounted%20a%20hate-ripened%20and%20politically-driven%20rebellion%20against%20the%20state%20and%20state%20institutions.%E2%80%9D%20Imran%20Khan%20himself%20has%20been%20booked%20under%20the%20stringent%20Anti-Terrorism%20Act%2C%20over%20the%20attack%20on%20the%20army%20GHQ.%20Since%20the%20military%20crackdown%2C%20leaders%20have%20been%20deserting%20the%20PTI%20in%20droves%3B%2057%20of%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20party%20members%20announced%20they%20were%20forming%20their%20party%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20parliamentarians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20and%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20imprisonment%20have%20raised%20suspicions%20that%20the%20state%20was%20in%20a%20hurry%20to%20disqualify%20Khan%20from%20the%20upcoming%20general%20election.%C2%A0%3Cem%3EC%3C%2Fem%3Eould%20Khan%20still%20pose%20a%20risk%20to%20his%20rivals%20by%20supporting%20other%20candidates%20from%20behind%20bars%3F%C2%A0%20In%20a%20video%20recorded%20before%20his%20arrest%20and%20posted%20on%20social%20media%2C%20Khan%20again%20called%20on%20his%20supporters%20to%20take%20to%20the%20streets%20in%20protest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fallout%20with%20Khan%2C%20the%20attack%20on%20military%20sites%20and%20the%20subsequent%20military%20trials%20of%20civilians%2C%20all%20point%20towards%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20problematic%20military%20of%20Pakistan%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20letting%20its%20grip%20over%20politics%20ease.%20The%20nation%20is%20notorious%20for%20jailing%20former%20prime%20ministers%2C%20be%20it%20Hussain%20Shaheed%20Suhrawardy%2C%20Zulfikar%20Ali%20Bhutto%2C%20Benazir%20Bhutto%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20and%20now%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20and%20avoiding%20any%20action%20against%20the%20military.%20Even%20as%20the%20five-year%20term%20of%20the%20National%20Assembly%20was%20coming%20to%20a%20close%2C%20legislation%20amending%20the%20Official%20Secrets%20Act%20bill%2C%20which%20amplifies%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20Inter-Services%20Intelligence%20(ISI)%2C%20was%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20interesting%20twist%3A%20will%20self-exiled%2C%20three-time%20former%20PM%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ede%20facto%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0head%20of%20PML-N%2C%20return%20to%20Pakistan%20to%20lead%20its%20election%20campaign%3F%20In%20late%20June%2C%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20National%20Assembly%20passed%20a%20bill%20to%20limit%20the%20lifetime%20disqualification%20of%20lawmakers%20to%20five%20years%2C%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20the%20return%20of%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20from%20London%20to%20resume%20active%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20popular%20demand%20for%20general%20elections%20is%20gaining%20momentum%20in%20Pakistan.%20Further%20delaying%20of%20elections%20carries%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20political%20uncertainty.%20A%20day%20ago%2C%20PM%20Sharif%20recommended%20the%20dissolution%20of%20parliament.%20Amidst%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20arrest%2C%20military%20institutionalisation%2C%20economic%20chaos%2C%20soaring%20inflation%2C%20an%20acute%20shortage%20of%20gas%20and%20electricity%20and%20a%20general%20state%20of%20despair%2C%20outgoing%20PM%20Sharif%20has%20announced%20the%20auction%20of%20Toshakhana%20gifts%2C%20the%20proceeds%20of%20which%20would%20be%20spent%20on%20welfare%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVaishali%20Basu%20Sharma%20is%20an%20analyst%20of%20strategic%20and%20economic%20affairs.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691663747000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F07221444%2FScreenshot-2023-06-07-at-10.13.10-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-election-military-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20fallout%20with%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20the%20attack%20on%20military%20sites%20and%20the%20subsequent%20military%20trials%20of%20civilians%2C%20all%20point%20towards%20the%20fact%20that%20no%20such%20plan%20is%20afoot.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-election-military-politics%22%2C%22cd