a%20legislative%20assembly%20has%20passed%20a%20unanimous%20resolution%2C%20urging%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20rename%20the%20state%20as%20%E2%80%98Keralam%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20constitution%20and%20all%20official%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20minister%20Pinarayi%20Vijayan%20moved%20the%20resolution%20in%20the%20assembly%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20August%209%2C%20which%20was%20accepted%20without%20opposition%20from%20any%20of%20the%20lawmakers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20name%20of%20our%20state%20in%20Malayalam%20is%20Keralam.%20States%20were%20formed%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20language%20on%20November%201%2C%201956.%20That%20day%20is%20also%20observed%20as%20Kerala%20formation%20day.%20The%20demand%20for%20a%20united%20Kerala%20for%20all%20Malayalam-speaking%20communities%20has%20been%20strongly%20raised%20right%20from%20the%20days%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle.%20However%2C%20the%20name%20of%20our%20state%20in%20the%20First%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution%20has%20been%20written%20as%20Kerala.%20This%20Assembly%20is%20unanimously%20requesting%20the%20Union%20Government%20to%20take%20immediate%20steps%20under%20Article%203%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20change%20the%20name%20of%20the%20state%20to%20Keralam%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkerala%2Fkerala-assembly-unanimously-passes-resolution-to-change-official-name-of-state-to-keralam%2Farticle67175490.ece%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%203%20in%20the%20constitution%20deals%20with%20the%20formation%20of%20new%20states%20and%20the%20alteration%20of%20areas%2C%20boundaries%2C%20or%20names%20of%20existing%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-politics%2Fkerala-to-rename-keralam-origin-8884600%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20there%20are%20several%20theories%20about%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20name%20%E2%80%98Kerala%E2%80%99.%20It%20says%20the%20earliest%20epigraphic%20record%20that%20mentions%20Kerala%20is%20emperor%20Asoka%E2%80%99s%20Rock%20Edict%20II%20of%20257%20BC.%C2%A0%20The%20inscription%20refers%20to%20the%20local%20ruler%20as%20Keralaputra%20(Sanskrit%20for%20%E2%80%9Cson%20of%20Kerala%E2%80%9D)%2C%20and%20also%20%E2%80%9Cson%20of%20Chera%E2%80%9D%20referring%20to%20the%20Chera%20dynasty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20movement%20for%20the%20unification%20of%20Malayalam-speaking%20regions%20had%20been%20gathering%20momentum%20since%20the%201920s%2C%20which%20called%20for%20the%20merger%20of%20Malabar%2C%20Kochi%2C%20and%20Travancore%20into%20one%20territory.%20On%20July%201%2C%201949%2C%20two%20princely%20states%20of%20Travancore%20and%20Kochi%20were%20integrated%2C%20resulting%20in%20the%20formation%20of%20Travancore-Cochin%20state.%20Later%2C%20on%20November%201%2C%201956%2C%20the%20present-day%20Kerala%20came%20into%20being%2C%20in%20line%20with%20the%20formation%20of%20linguistic%20states.%20The%20Syed%20Fazl%20Ali%20Commission%20recommended%20that%20states%20be%20reorganised%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20a%20common%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20is%20not%20necessary%20for%20renaming%20cities%2C%20however%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20renaming%20states%2C%20the%20Union%20home%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20nod%20is%20mandatory.%20A%20constitutional%20amendment%20is%20necessary%20for%20such%20a%20change%20to%20take%20effect%2C%20requiring%20parliamentary%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20proposal%20is%20received%20from%20the%20state%20government%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20begins%20its%20process.%20It%20seeks%20No%20Objection%20Certificates%20(NOCs)%20from%20several%20agencies%20such%20as%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Railways%2C%20Intelligence%20Bureau%2C%20Department%20of%20Posts%2C%20Survey%20of%20India%2C%20and%20Registrar%20General%20of%20India%20to%20allow%20such%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20proposal%20is%20accepted%2C%20the%20resolution%2C%20introduced%20as%20a%20Bill%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20becomes%20a%20law%20and%20the%20name%20of%20the%20state%20is%20changed%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691652659000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F28124329%2Fdc-Cover-j5v1mqcmbp6o50fqg1vstj84n2-20160628134359.Medi_.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkerala-assembly-passes-unanimous-resolution-to-rename-state-as-keralam-writes-to-centre%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20'Keralam'%20is%20the%20accepted%20and%20common%20usage%20in%20Malayalam%2C%20the%20state%20is%20generally%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98Kerala'%20in%20official%20records%2C%20especially%20those%20in%20English.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fkerala-assembly-passes-unanimous-resolution-to-rename-state-as-keralam-writes-to-centre%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Identifies%20New%20Coronavirus%20%E2%80%98Variant%20of%20Interest'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F10125346%2F1024px-World_Health_Organization_Flag.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fworld-health-organization%2Ft-38396203%5C%22%3EWorld%20Health%20Organisation%20(WHO)%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday%20classified%20a%20new%20strain%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fcovid-19%2Ft-62123668%5C%22%3ECOVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cvariant%20of%20interest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EG.5%20variant%20has%20been%20spreading%20rapidly%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funited-states-of-america%2Ft-19065189%5C%22%3EUnited%20States%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20encompassing%20over%