an%3EIn%20April%202022%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fas-imran-loses-trust-vote-shehbaz-sharif-emerges-frontrunner-for-pak-pms-post%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKhan%20was%20ousted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20prime%20minister%20after%20a%20parliamentary%20vote%20of%20no%20confidence%20by%20the%20joint%20opposition%20alliance.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20is%20currently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-66414696%5C%22%3Ejailed%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20being%20sentenced%20for%20corruption%20allegations.%20After%20the%20conviction%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F08%2F08%2Fasia%2Fpakistan-imran-khan-disqualified-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Edisqualified%20him%20from%20running%20for%20office%20for%20five%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20month%20earlier%2C%20senior%20State%20Department%20official%20Donald%20Lu%20attended%20a%20lunch%20for%20outgoing%20Pakistani%20ambassador%20Asad%20Majeed%20Khan%20at%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20residence%20in%20Washington.%20The%20alleged%20diplomatic%20cable%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20political%20controversy%20was%20based%20on%20the%20discussions%20at%20the%20lunch%20sent%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%20to%20headquarters%20in%20Islamabad.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20start%20of%20the%20discussions%2C%20as%20per%20the%20note%20published%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EIntercept%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Lu%20conveyed%20that%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20unhappiness%20over%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20policy%20on%20Ukraine.%20Russia%20had%20begun%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20on%20February%2024%2C%20just%20as%20Imran%20Khan%20was%20enroute%20Moscow%20on%20a%20state%20visit.%20Thereafter%2C%20Pakistan%20had%20also%20abstained%20on%20various%20UN%20resolutions%20that%20criticised%20Russia%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20note%20stated%20that%20Lu%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cquite%20clear%20that%20this%20is%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20policy%E2%80%9D%2C%20indicating%20that%20the%20military%20establishment%20was%20not%20on%20the%20same%20page.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELu%20added%20that%20the%20view%20was%20that%20this%20policy%20over%20Russia%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctied%20to%20the%20current%20political%20dramas%20in%20Islamabad%20that%20he%20(Prime%20Minister)%20needs%20and%20is%20trying%20to%20show%20a%20public%20face%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Pakistani%20ambassador%20apparently%20responded%20that%20this%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20correct%20reading%20of%20the%20developments.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20following%20key%20excerpt%20from%20the%20diplomatic%20cable%20is%20where%20Lu%20refers%20to%20the%20disenchantment%20over%20Khan.%20He%20conveyed%2C%20as%20per%20the%20version%20transcribed%20by%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%2C%20that%20if%20Khan%20lost%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%2C%20it%20will%20be%20easier%20for%20US%20and%20its%20western%20allies%20to%20quickly%20mend%20frayed%20diplomatic%20ties%20with%20Pakistan%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20asked%20Don%20if%20the%20reason%20for%20a%20strong%20U.S.%20reaction%20was%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20abstention%20in%20the%20voting%20in%20the%20UNGA.%20He%20categorically%20replied%20in%20the%20negative%20and%20said%20that%20it%20was%20due%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Moscow.%20He%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20if%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%20against%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20succeeds%2C%20all%20will%20be%20forgiven%20in%20Washington%20because%20the%20Russia%20visit%20is%20being%20looked%20at%20as%20a%20decision%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%20Otherwise%2C%20I%20think%20it%20will%20be%20tough%20going%20ahead.%E2%80%9D%20He%20paused%20and%20then%20said%20%E2%80%9CI%20cannot%20tell%20how%20this%20will%20be%20seen%20by%20Europe%20but%20I%20suspect%20their%20reaction%20will%20be%20similar.%E2%80%9D%20He%20then%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Chonestly%20I%20think%20isolation%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20will%20become%20very%20strong%20from%20Europe%20and%20the%20United%20States.%E2%80%9D%20Don%20further%20commented%20that%20it%20seemed%20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Moscow%20was%20planned%20during%20the%20Beijing%20Olympics%20and%20there%20was%20an%20attempt%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20meet%20Putin%20which%20was%20not%20successful%20and%20then%20this%20idea%20was%20hatched%20that%20he%20would%20go%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20another%20part%20of%20the%20published%20cable%2C%20the%20Pakistani%20diplomat%20accused%20the%20US%20of%20being%20tougher%20on%20Pakistan%20while%20going%20easy%20on%20India%20%E2%80%93%20which%20had%20also%20taken%20a%20neutral%20position%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDon%20was%20evasive%20and%20responded%20that%20Washington%20looked%20at%20the%20U.S.-India%20relationship%20very%20much%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20China.%20He%20added%20that%20while%20India%20had%20a%20close%20relationship%20with%20Moscow%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20we%20will%20actually%20see%20a%20change%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20policy%20once%20all%20Indian%20students%20are%20out%20of%20Ukraine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20article%20also%20said%20that%20the%20document%20was%20%E2%80%9Cprovided%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EIntercept%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20an%20anonymous%20source%20in%20the%20Pakistani%20military%20who%20said%20that%20they%20had%20no%20ties%20to%20Imran%20Khan%20or%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20party%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1769320%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EDawn%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20this%20disclaimer%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Intercept%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20source%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmany%20believe%20that%20the%20source%20of%20the%20leak%20could%20be%20the%20PTI%20itself%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20said%20that%20timing%20of%20the%20alleged%20cable%E2%80%99s%20publication%20%E2%80%9Cseems%20quite%20significant%2C%20as%20it%20comes%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1768528%5C%22%3Eimprisonment%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20Imran%20Khan%20over%20charges%20of%20graft%20in%20the%20Toshakhana%20case%E2%80%9D.%20It%20noted%20that%20as%20per%20protocol%2C%20only%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20senior%20officials%20had%20access%20to%20the%20confidential%20cable%2C%20which%20included%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20foreign%20minister%20and%20army%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Pakistan%20government%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20ended%20at%20Wednesday%20midnight%2C%20he%20said%20that%20during%3C%2Fspan%3E%20two%20meetings%20of%20the%20National%20Security%20Committee%20on%20the%20cypher%20were%20held%20under%20his%20leadership.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20one%20of%20the%20meetings%2C%20former%20ambassador%20and%20foreign%20secretary%20Asad%20Majeed%20clearly%20stated%20that%20there%20was%20no%20discussion%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20in%20his%20meeting%20with%20Donald%20Lu%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20if%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20cypher%20are%20true%20and%20they%20were%20published%20in%20an%20international%20media%20outlet%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthen%20it%20is%20a%20massive%20crime%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRanaSanaullahPK%2Fstatus%2F1689354884762710016%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERana%20Sanaullah%20Khan%2C%20interior%20minister%20in%20Sharif%20cabinet%2C%20tweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20there%20had%20to%20be%20an%20investigation%20to%20establish%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20document.%20%E2%80%9CPotentially%2C%20it%20is%20a%20very%20sinister%2C%20treacherous%2C%20and%20seditious%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThough%20there%20is%20nothing%20new%20in%20this%20story%2C%20the%20investigation%20needs%20to%20held%20to%20establish%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20information%20or%20source%20document.%20Potentially%2C%20it%20is%20a%20very%20sinister%2C%20treacherous%2C%20and%20seditious%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(1%2F2)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Rana%20SanaUllah%20Khan%20(%40RanaSanaullahPK)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FRanaSanaullahPK%2Fstatus%2F1689354884762710016%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%209%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndicating%20that%20the%20article%20could%20be%20the%20basis%20of%20further%20action%2C%20the%20interior%20minister%20noted%20that%20Khan%20had%20stated%20that%20he%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccopy%20of%20the%20cypher%2C%20which%20he%20has%20not%20returned%20and%20has%20accepted%20(on%20record)%20that%20he%20misplaced%20or%20lost%20it%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20proven%20guilty%2C%20Khan%20should%20be%20tried%20under%20the%20Official%20Secret%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20tweeted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fbriefings%2Fdepartment-press-briefing-august-9-2023%2F%23post-469814-Pakistan2%5C%22%3EAt%20a%20media%20briefing%20on%20Wednesday%20in%20Washington%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20US%20State%20department%20spokesperson%20Mathew%20Miller%20confirmed%20that%20the%20US%20had%20expressed%20its%20concern%20both%20privately%20and%20publicly%20about%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20express%20concern%20privately%20to%20the%20Government%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20as%20we%20express%20concern%20publicly%2C%20about%20the%20visit%20of%20then%20Prime%20Minister%20Khan%20to%20Moscow%20on%20the%20very%20day%20of%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20We%20made%20that%20concern%20quite%20clear%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20response%20to%20a%20media%20query.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20refusing%20to%20authenticate%20the%20document%2C%20Miller%20added%20that%20the%20comments%20in%20the%20published%20note%20%E2%80%9Cwere%20accurate%20as%20reported%2C%20they%20in%20no%20way%20show%20the%20United%20States%20taking%20a%20position%20on%20who%20the%20leader%20of%20Pakistan%20ought%20to%20be%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20allegations%20that%20the%20United%20States%20has%20interfered%20in%20internal%20decisions%20about%20the%20leadership%20of%20Pakistan%20are%20false%2C%20as%20we%20have%20stated%20they%20were%20false.%20They%20were%20always%20false%20and%20they%20remain%20false%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20remarks%20could%20be%20construed%20as%20regime%20change%20due%20to%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20history%20of%20ousting%20leaders%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20Miller%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20will%20say%20that%20I%20can%20understand%20how%20those%20comments%2C%20number%20one%2C%20could%20be%20taken%20out%20of%20context%3B%20and%20number%20two%2C%20how%20people%20might%20have%20the%20desire%20for%20them%20to%20be%20taken%20out%20of%20context%2C%20and%20might%20try%20to%20use%20them%20to%20advance%20an%20agenda%20that%20is%20not%20represented%20by%20the%20comments%20themselves.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1682150%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Khan%20had%20first%20mentioned%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20plot%E2%80%9D%20when%20he%20wave%20a%20document%20and%20claimed%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccredible%20proof%E2%80%9D%20of%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20remove%20him%20from%20office.%20On%20March%2031%2C%20his%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.voanews.com%2Famp%2Fpakistan-sends-us-demarche-over-alleged-political-meddling%2F6511766.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eissued%20a%20demarche%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20the%20US%20embassy%20to%20make%20a%20formal%20protest%20that%20the%20United%20States%20had%20backed%20the%20opposition%20on%20the%20no-confidence%20vote.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20state%20department%20had%20then%20said%20that%20there%20%E2%80%9Cno%20truth%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20allegations%20made%20by%20Khan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFour%20days%20later%2C%20in%20a%20televised%20address%20to%20his%20party%20lawmakers%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dawn.com%2Fnews%2F1683362%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EKhan%20named%20US%20Assistant%20Secretary%20of%20State%20for%20South%20and%20Central%20Asian%20Affairs%20Donald%20Lu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20having%20reportedly%20warn%20in%20a%20meeting%20with%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20Ambassador%20to%20the%20US%2C%20Asad%20Majeed%20that%20there%20could%20be%20implications%20if%20he%20survived%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20no-confidence%20motion%20in%20the%20National%20Assembly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20Khan%20had%20this%20February%20gone%20back%20on%20his%20earlier%20allegations%20targeting%20the%20United%20States%20and%20accused%20former%20army%20chief%20Qamar%20Javed%20Bajwa%20for%20being%20responsible%20for%20his%20ouster.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhatever%20happened%2C%20now%20as%20things%20unfold%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20US%20who%20told%20Pakistan%20%5Bto%20oust%20me%5D.%20It%20was%20unfortunately%2C%20from%20what%20evidence%20has%20come%20up%2C%20%5Bformer%20army%20chief%5D%20Gen%20%5BQamar%20Javed%5D%20Bajwa%20who%20somehow%20managed%20to%20tell%20the%20Americans%20that%20I%20was%20anti-American.%20And%20so%2C%20it%20%